cs.IT, cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SI. 

This paper deals with the problem of cooperative data exchange, which involves information theory and networking concepts. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves game theory and mechanism design, which are covered in cs.GT (Game Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The use of broadcast channels and algorithms for finding solutions suggest cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as possible sub-categories as well.
